---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  description="Our privacy policy will help you understand what information is collected and how it is used."
  title="Privacy policy Â· Cloudcode"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 sm:py-20 lg:px-8">
    <div class="sm:pb:20 flex flex-col gap-4 pb-16 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-base">Last update: July 31, 2023</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="mb-4">
        At CloudCode, we prioritize your privacy and are committed to safeguarding your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information, and our commitment to not accessing your files without explicit consent.
      </p>
      <h2 class="mb-6 mt-12 text-xl font-medium sm:text-2xl">1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        We collect the following types of information:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-4">
        <li>
          Account Information: Name, email address, and other details you provide when creating or managing your account.
        </li>
        <li>
          Usage Data: Information about how you interact with our services, including your usage patterns and server configurations.
        </li>
        <li>
          File Data: Any files you upload or store within our platform.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h2 class="mb-6 mt-12 text-xl font-medium sm:text-2xl">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We may use your personal information for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-4">
        <li>
          To provide and manage our hosting and development services.
        </li>
        <li>
          To communicate important updates, support, and account information.
        </li>
        <li>
        To improve our services and address technical issues.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h2 class="mb-6 mt-12 text-xl font-medium sm:text-2xl">3. File Access and Consent</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Your files are your property. We will never access, modify, or view your files without your explicit consent, except in the following cases:</p>
      <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-4">
        <li>
          User Consent: If file access is required (e.g., for troubleshooting), we will request your consent beforehand.
        </li>
        <li>
          Support Requests: If you need technical assistance and file access is necessary, we will ask for your permission.
        </li>
        <li>
        Security and Legal Compliance: In certain cases, such as security breaches or legal obligations, we may access your files without prior consent, but we will notify you promptly.
        </li>
      <h2 class="mb-6 mt-12 text-xl font-medium sm:text-2xl">4. Sharing of Information</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We will not share your personal data or files with third parties except in the following circumstances:</p>
      <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-4">
        <li>
          Legal Compliance: We may share your information if required by law or to protect our legal rights.
        </li>
        <li>
          Third-Party Service Providers: We may share data with trusted providers who perform services like payment processing or email communication, but they cannot use your information for other purposes.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h2 class="mb-6 mt-12 text-xl font-medium sm:text-2xl">5. Your Rights</h2>
      <p class="mb-4"> You have the following rights regarding your personal data::</p>
      <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-4">
        <li>
          Access and Control: You can access, update, or delete your personal data by logging into your CloudCode account.
        </li>
        <li>
          Consent Withdrawal: You may withdraw your consent to access your files at any time. However, this may impact our ability to assist you with certain requests.
        </li>
        <li>
        Data Deletion: You can request the deletion of your data by contacting us. We will delete your personal data and files as per our data retention policy.
         </li>
      </ul>
      <h2 class="mb-6 mt-12 text-xl font-medium sm:text-2xl">6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
      We will retain your personal data and files only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this policy or as required by law. Once your data is no longer needed, we will securely delete it.</p>
      <h2 class="mb-6 mt-12 text-xl font-medium sm:text-2xl">7. Security Measures</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We use industry-standard security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.</p>
      <h2 class="mb-6 mt-12 text-xl font-medium sm:text-2xl">8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices. Any changes will be posted on our website, and we will notify you of significant updates. Please review this policy periodically.</p>
      <h2 class="mb-6 mt-12 text-xl font-medium sm:text-2xl">Contact Us</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        If you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy, please contact us at
        our discord (https://discord.gg/U7aFkZWk74).
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
